---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Terms of Use | WarningLightMeaning.com';
const description = 'Terms of use for WarningLightMeaning.com. By using this site you agree to these terms.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-8">Last updated: June 2025</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>By accessing and using WarningLightMeaning.com, you accept and agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use this site.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Informational Purpose Only</h2>
        <p>All content on WarningLightMeaning.com is provided for general informational purposes only. The information on this site is not professional automotive advice. Always consult a qualified mechanic or automotive professional before making decisions about your vehicle. We are not responsible for any damage, injury, or loss resulting from actions taken based on information found on this site.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Accuracy of Information</h2>
        <p>We make every effort to ensure the information on this site is accurate and up to date. However, vehicle warning lights and their meanings can vary by make, model, and year. Always refer to your vehicle owner's manual for authoritative information specific to your car.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content on this site including text, graphics, and layout is the property of WarningLightMeaning.com unless otherwise noted. You may not reproduce, distribute, or republish content from this site without prior written permission.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>WarningLightMeaning.com and its operators shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of this site or reliance on any information provided herein.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">6. External Links</h2>
        <p>This site may contain links to third-party websites. These links are provided for convenience only. We have no control over the content of those sites and accept no responsibility for them.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">7. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes your acceptance of the new terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">8. Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these terms? Use our <a href="/contact/" class="text-amber-600 hover:text-amber-700 font-medium">contact page</a>.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
